race.comment: WILL ONE (1) is a son of Rubick on debut and caught the eye with a stylish trial win on his home track. Looks forward enough to make an immediate impact. SURPRISATIC (2) closed off strongly first-up at Canberra when third after settling well back. The extra trip is ideal and he looms as the danger. FIRE CHAT (6) found the line well on debut at Gundagai. Freshened and could be storming late again. READY TO RUSH (3) debuts for the Matty Dale stable and showed ability with a Kembla Grange trial placing. Well drawn and looks set to run a race. RAINING VIOLETS (9) is by Casino Prince and arrives off a solid trial effort. Market watch advised.
